/PG844/XX/PR

/KAJerusalem, Jerusalem (Jerusalem of Gold)/PR

/ITThis translation can be sung to the same melody as the Hebrew./PR

/PR

The olive trees that stand in silence/PR

Up on the hills of time,/PR

To hear the voices of the city/PR

As bells of evening chime./PR

/PR

The Shofar sounding from the Temple/PR

To call the world to prayer,/PR

The shepherd pauses in the valley/PR

And peace is everywhere./PR

/PR

The water well for those who thirsted,/PR

The ancient market square,/PR

Your golden sun that lights the future/PR

For people everywhere./PR

How many songs,/PR

How many stories,/PR

The stony hills recall./PR

Around her heart my city carries/PR

A lonely ancient wall./PR

/PR

And far away beyond the desert/PR

A thousand suns will glow./PR

We shall be going to the Jordan,/PR

By way of Jericho./PR

My simple voice cannot acclaim thee,/PR

Too weak the words I choose,/PR

Jerusalem, if I forget thee,/PR

May my right hand its cunning lose./PR

/PR

Jerusalem, Jerusalem,/PR

Forever young, yet forever old,/PR

My heart will sing your songs of glory, Jerusalem./PR

Jerusalem, Jerusalem,/PR

Oh, city with a heart of gold,/PR

My heart will sing your songs of glory, Jerusalem./PR

Naomi Shemer (translated by Norman Newell)/XX/PR

