/PL849/XXSONGS/XX/PR

/KATHIS LAND IS YOUR LAND/XX/PR

This land is your land, this land is my land/PR

From California to the New York Island/PR

From the redwood forest to the Gulf Stream waters/PR

This land was made for you and me./PR

/PR


As I was walkinò that ribbon of highway/PR


I saw above me that endless skyway/PR


I saw below me that golden valley/PR


I said this land was made for you and me./PR

/PR

Iòve roamed and rambled and I followed my/PR


footsteps/PR

To the sparkling sound of her diamond desert/PR

And all around me, a voice was sounding:/PR

This land was made for you and me./PR

/PR


Down in the city, in the shadow of the steeple/PR


By the relief office, I saw my people/PR


As they stood there hungry I stood there/PR



whistling: This land was made for you and me./PR

/PR


Nobody living can ever stop me/PR


As I go walking my freedom highway/PR


Nobody living can make me turn back,/PR


cuz this land was made for you and me./PR

/PR

The sun came shining, and I was strolling/PR

And the wheat fields waving and the dust cloud/PR


rolling/PR

As the fog was lifting, a voice was chanting/PR

This land was made for you and me./PR

Woody Guthrie/XX/PR

